PHENOTYPE: Shoot apical meristem cells of embryos are highly vacuolated; light-grown seedling development is severely affected (lethal), seedlings have open purple cotyledons, short roots and no shoot is produced; dark-grown seedlings resemble light-grown wild-type seedlings having short hypocotyl, open and enlarged cotyledons, accumulation of anthocyanins, chloroplast-like plastid differentiation; expression of light-induced genes in dark-grown plants.

Seedlings screened in bulk via high throughput methods for responses to various stressors. Results  are in comparison to Col-0.heat:no change,cold:no change,oxidative stress:decreased,osmotic stress:increased,salt stress:increased,ABA:no change,hypoxia:ND.
Delayed flowering and reduced root growth.
Delayed flowering and reduced root growth. Reduction in RNA-directed DNA methylation.
Delayed flowering. Flowers 2 days later when grown in LD conditions.
